
ANSIBLE for CONF. MANAGEMENT & DEPLOYMENTS

- Introduction

IT Automation, conf. management, provisioning tool

Uses PlayBooks to deploy,manage,build, test

- Differences with other Tools

Chef/Puppet
	- Work with 'Master' server in the setup.
	Ansible works with SSH and does not have a 'master'.

Workflow/Push vs PUll
	- Since most conf. manag. tools have a 'master' server they use PULL method to retrieve data.
	Ansible uses the PUSH method requiring no Client installation or configuration.

- Order
	Ansible uses pure order execution.
	Puppet in not applied in order.

- Language
	Ansible is written upon Python
	Pupper is written in Ruby

- Syntax
	Ansible is based in YAML
	Puppet is based on DSL
